---
import Feature from '../../layouts/Feature.astro';
import { keys } from '../../lib/keybindings';
---

<Feature
  title="MULTIPLEXER"
  subtitle="Splits, tabs, and floating panes. No tmux required."
>
  <h2>Pane Splits</h2>
  <p>Split any pane to run multiple shells side by side. Splits can be nested as deep as you like.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.splitRight}</kbd> — Split right</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.splitDown}</kbd> — Split down</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.focusPaneDir}</kbd> — Focus pane by direction</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.resizePane}</kbd> — Resize pane</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.equalizePanes}</kbd> — Equalize all panes</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.zoomPane}</kbd> — Zoom/unzoom focused pane</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Dividers are draggable. Close a pane with <kbd>{keys.closePane}</kbd> and the remaining panes expand to fill the space.</p>

  <h2>Floating Panes</h2>
  <p>Any pane can become a floating overlay that sits on top of your splits. Drag, resize, and stack floating panes freely. Toggle between floating and tiled with a single keystroke.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.toggleFloating}</kbd> — Toggle floating pane</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.floatTileToggle}</kbd> — Move pane between floating and tiled</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Floating panes snap to edges and enforce minimum dimensions.</p>

  <h2>Undo / Redo Layout</h2>
  <p>Every split, close, and layout change is recorded. Made a mistake? Just undo it.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.undoSplit}</kbd> — Undo last split/close</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.redoSplit}</kbd> — Redo</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The full history of your layout changes is preserved for the session.</p>

  <h2>Tabs</h2>
  <p>Chrome-style tab management. Tabs can be torn off into new windows, dragged back in, and reordered with smooth animation.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><kbd>{keys.newTab}</kbd> — New tab</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.closeTab}</kbd> — Close tab</li>
    <li><kbd>{keys.nextTab}</kbd> / <kbd>{keys.prevTab}</kbd> — Next/previous tab</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Multi-Window</h2>
  <p>Open multiple windows and drag tabs between them. Each window gets proper HiDPI handling.</p>
</Feature>
